summary: This is an FBI 302 form documenting a delayed response to an additional inquiry from the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services regarding a search of the Interstate Identification Index (III) for records related to the Epstein case. The document indicates that records can be obtained through the III using the appropriate NCIC transaction.

persons.name: Michael C. Green
persons.role: Executive Deputy Commissioner of the NYS Division of Criminal Justice Services
persons.context: He is listed as the executive deputy commissioner of the NYS Division of Criminal Justice Services, which is the agency responding to the FBI's inquiry.

events.title: Delayed Response to Additional Inquiry
events.description: The FBI's New York office receives a delayed response from the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services regarding a search of the Interstate Identification Index (III) for records.

locations: Alfred E. Smith Building, 80 South Swan St. Albany, New York 12210
keyFacts: The document is a delayed response from the New York State Division of Criminal Justice Services to an FBI inquiry regarding a search of the Interstate Identification Index (III).
It indicates that records can be obtained through the III using the appropriate NCIC transaction.
The response is dated October 6, 2021, showing ongoing investigative activity related to the Epstein case at that time.
